Team 1: NLP and Digital Preservation Annotation Platform
Team Members: Riddhiman Puzari, Priya Saikia, Nandita Das

Your project focuses on building a platform to digitize, annotate, and preserve low-resource regional languages, creating clean datasets for future AI and LLM integration.

Key Research Areas
1. The Landscape of Low-Resource Languages: Research the current challenges in digital preservation, specifically focusing on tokenization, syntax categorization, and data scarcity.
2. Crowdsourcing & Annotation Models: Study existing platforms (e.g., Mozilla Common Voice) to understand how they gamify or incentivize users to submit and verify linguistic data.
3. Dataset Structuring for AI: Investigate how linguistic data must be structured and stored in a database so it can be effectively exported and utilized to train machine learning models.

Phase 1 Deliverables
1. A comparative study of at least three existing language preservation or annotation platforms.
2. A proposed database schema detailing how you will store phrases, translations, dialect metadata, and verification statuses.
3. Your recommended full-stack technology stack for building a secure, user-friendly portal.
